Database¶

The module of result database.

class autodse.database.Database(name: str, db_file_path: Optional[str] = None)¶

Base class of result database

db_id¶

A unique ID of this database.

log¶

Logger

db_file_path¶

Path to persist the database.

best_cache¶

A priority queue for best results.

code_hash_map¶

A dictionary to map code hash to the corresponding HLS result.

add_code_hash(code_hash: str, key: str) → Optional[str]¶

Add a new code hash to the map and check if it already exists.

Parameters

  • code_hash -- The code hash to be added.

  • key -- The key of the design point.

Returns

None if the code hash is new; otherwise the key with the same code hash.

batch_commit(pairs: List[Tuple[str, Any]]) → None¶

Commit a set of new results to the database.

Parameters

pairs -- A list of key-result pairs.

batch_commit_impl(pairs: List[Tuple[str, Any]]) → int¶

Batch commit function implementation.

Parameters

pairs -- A list of key-result pairs.

Returns

Indicate the number of committed data.

batch_query(keys: List[str]) → List[Optional[Any]]¶

Query for a list of the values by the given key list.

Parameters

key -- The key of a design point.

Returns

The result object of the corresponding key, or None if the key is unavailable.

commit(key: str, result: Any) → None¶

Commit a new result to the database.

Parameters

  • key -- The key of a design point.

  • result -- The result to be committed.

commit_impl(key: str, result: Any) → bool¶

Commit function implementation.

Parameters

  • key -- The key of a design point.

  • result -- The result to be committed.

Returns

True if the commit was success; otherwise False.

count() → int¶

Count total number of data points in the database.

Returns

Total number of data points

init_best_cache() → None¶

Initialize the best cache using the loaded data.

init_code_hash_map() → None¶

Initialize the code hash set using the loaded data.

load() → None¶

Load existing data from the given database and update the best cahce (if available).

persist() → bool¶

Persist the DB by dumping it to a pickle file and close the DB.

Returns

True if the dumping and close was success; otherwise False.

query(key: str) → Optional[Any]¶

Query for the value by the given key.

Parameters

key -- The key of a design point.

Returns

The result object of the corresponding key, or None if the key is unavailable.

query_all() → List[Any]¶

Query all values in the database.

Returns

All data in the database

query_keys() → List[str]¶

Return all keys

update_best(result: autodse.result.Result) → None¶

Check if the new result has the best QoR and update it if so.

Note

We allow value overwritten in the database for the performance issue, although it should not happen during the search. However, the best cache may keep the overrided result so this could be a potential issue.

Parameters

result -- The new result to be checked.

class autodse.database.PickleDatabase(name: str, db_file_path: Optional[str] = None)¶

The database implementation using PickleDB.

This is an alternative when other databases are unavailable in the system. Note that it is discouraged to use this database for DSE due to poor performance and the lack of multi-node support.

lock¶

The thread lock to achieve thread-safe.

database¶

The Pickle database.
